prompt:
Add a public function called GetListLength to Collections.calr that creates a list, adds items, and returns the count. It takes i32 parameter n (number of items to add) and returns i32.

Use this exact Calor count syntax:
§F{f001:GetListLength:pub}
  §I{i32:n}
  §O{i32}
  §Q (>= n 0)
  §LIST{items:i32}
  §/LIST{items}
  §L{l001:i:1:n:1}
    §PUSH{items} i
  §/L{l001}
  §R §CNT{items}
§/F{f001}

The syntax:
- §LIST{id:type} ... §/LIST{id} creates an empty or initialized list
- §PUSH{id} value adds to the list dynamically
- §CNT{collection} returns the count/length of a collection
